NPCs.

Use npcs to list visible non-player characters in your current room.

This command is useful when look gives too much information or when you want to
quickly know what creatures, shopkeepers, guards, quest givers, or monsters are
nearby.

Common forms:

npcs
  List visible NPCs in the room.

look <npc>
  Look more closely at one NPC from the list.

kill <npc>
  Start combat with an NPC, if combat is allowed.

If several visible NPCs have the same name, the command condenses them and gives
a count.
